<blockquote>
<p>EDIT: 2 small comments.<br />
Firstly, I actually made an image that I wanted to include, but I'm shit with computers and IDK how to properly link images, so it ended up just leaving the website i used to make the image rather than the image itself (at least, thats how its showing up on my end). The original image was a &quot;deep-fried&quot; mr. Krabs meme with multiple layers of impact font on the top and bottom, with the top layers saying &quot;WHEN THE COOL KIDS AT GAMERS AGAINST WEED / DON'T SHOW UP FOR THE INTERVIEW&quot;. I just wanted to clarify that.<br />
Secondly, my understanding was that the whole point of these GoI interviews was to sort of flanderize them for the lolfoundation universe, hence why its just &quot;dumb meme chat rooms lol&quot;. Because thats what people who flanderize GAW usu portray them as. I just wanted to clarify my reasoning.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In this situation, I think you can use the reply function instead of edit. It was difficult to notice this, and it makes me feel like I'm double-posting this one comment.</p>
<p>Onto your edit, your proposed addition does not really directly reference GAW. As it looks, it seems more like linking to a meme site generically (that can be about GAW, but not explicitly about GAW).</p>
<p>i.e. My gripe is that it is not directly talking about GAW. You can argue that there is an implication, but the other entries don't make it subtle over the GoIs they're flanderising.</p>
<p>I suppose the image file would work, but the URL you listed does not actually link to the image you've made. Do consult Google when in doubt over how to link images in this website (or consult the <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/how-to-write-an-scp#toc2">Formatting</a> tab regarding image uploading).</p>

